# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "Measuring real GDP holds prices constant or adjusts the value of the nation’s output to higher or lower prices that may have prevailed from earlier years (using the GDP deflator price index). In this way the real GDP represents the actual amount of the nation’s output; which if it has increased indicates that the typical person now has more goods and services available, a result generally believed to lead to higher living standards."
