# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "**Economic thinking in your daily life**"
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/economics-finance-domain/ap-macroeconomics-staging/holding-area-for-unruly-questions/non-ap-style-questions/a/12-how-does-the-ppc-show-scarcity">http://translate.khanacademy.org/economics-finance-domain/ap-macroeconomics-staging/holding-area-for-unruly-questions/non-ap-style-questions/a/12-how-does-the-ppc-show-scarcity</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid ""
"- Scarcity is the fundamental problem in economics: faced with scarce resources, what choices do we make?\n"
"- The PPC is a model used to show the tradeoffs associated with allocating resources.\n"
"- The PPC helps us see *all* of the combinations of goods that can be produced\n"
"- Efficiencies are anything that falls on the PPC line.\n"
"- Inefficiencies are anything on the interior of the PPC bowed line"
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/economics-finance-domain/ap-macroeconomics-staging/holding-area-for-unruly-questions/non-ap-style-questions/a/12-how-does-the-ppc-show-scarcity">http://translate.khanacademy.org/economics-finance-domain/ap-macroeconomics-staging/holding-area-for-unruly-questions/non-ap-style-questions/a/12-how-does-the-ppc-show-scarcity</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "And while that question is interesting, even more fascinating is the way in which economist answer it. Thankfully, economists have a great model that helps them better illustrate and understand scarcity: the **production possibilities curve (PPC)**. "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/economics-finance-domain/ap-macroeconomics-staging/holding-area-for-unruly-questions/non-ap-style-questions/a/12-how-does-the-ppc-show-scarcity">http://translate.khanacademy.org/economics-finance-domain/ap-macroeconomics-staging/holding-area-for-unruly-questions/non-ap-style-questions/a/12-how-does-the-ppc-show-scarcity</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "Anything on the interior of the line is **inefficient**, meaning it’s not reaching the full potential of what could be produced. If Maxistan only produces $2$ tons of oranges and $2$ hoverboards, we would tell them: But you could be producing so much more! Why? Because they are not using all of their available resources to produce to their full potential."
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/economics-finance-domain/ap-macroeconomics-staging/holding-area-for-unruly-questions/non-ap-style-questions/a/12-how-does-the-ppc-show-scarcity">http://translate.khanacademy.org/economics-finance-domain/ap-macroeconomics-staging/holding-area-for-unruly-questions/non-ap-style-questions/a/12-how-does-the-ppc-show-scarcity</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "But why can’t Maxistan have an abundance of hovering *and* vitamin C? Because, like every country, Maxistan has limited resources. “Limited resources” means there is only so much **labor, land, capital, and entrepreneurial skill** in an economy, and those things are needed to make goods. "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/economics-finance-domain/ap-macroeconomics-staging/holding-area-for-unruly-questions/non-ap-style-questions/a/12-how-does-the-ppc-show-scarcity">http://translate.khanacademy.org/economics-finance-domain/ap-macroeconomics-staging/holding-area-for-unruly-questions/non-ap-style-questions/a/12-how-does-the-ppc-show-scarcity</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "Figure 1: Two extremes of production"
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/economics-finance-domain/ap-macroeconomics-staging/holding-area-for-unruly-questions/non-ap-style-questions/a/12-how-does-the-ppc-show-scarcity">http://translate.khanacademy.org/economics-finance-domain/ap-macroeconomics-staging/holding-area-for-unruly-questions/non-ap-style-questions/a/12-how-does-the-ppc-show-scarcity</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
